Not sure if related to this issue (or even to this topology) but I notice there were/are multiple eucalyptus-cloud processes running on these setups:

{code}
# netstat -nulp | grep :53
udp        0      0 10.107.105.143:53       0.0.0.0:*                           17194/eucalyptus-cl 
udp        0      0 10.111.5.143:53         0.0.0.0:*                           17194/eucalyptus-cl 
udp        0      0 10.107.105.143:53       0.0.0.0:*                           14916/eucalyptus-cl 
udp        0      0 10.111.5.143:53         0.0.0.0:*                           14916/eucalyptus-cl 
{code}

{code}
# ps aux | grep eucalyptus-cloud
root     13818  0.0  0.0 112648   976 pts/0    S+   09:39   0:00 grep --color=auto eucalyptus-cloud
eucalyp+ 14916  6.7 39.1 9517564 3131932 ?     Sl   Jun08  83:46 eucalyptus-cloud
root     17191  0.0  0.0  13788     8 ?        Ss   Jun08   0:00 eucalyptus-cloud
eucalyp+ 17194  5.8 39.5 9737224 3164348 ?     Sl   Jun08  72:15 eucalyptus-cloud
{code}

{code}
# cat /var/run/eucalyptus/eucalyptus-cloud.pid 
17194
{code}

this may be related to the fix for EUCA-12410
